#. <section class="sutta" id="sn35.60"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.60:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.60:0.2"
msgid "6. Avijjāvagga"
msgstr "6. Ignorance"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 60. Sabbupādānapariññāsutta → sabbūpādānapariññāsuttaṃ (bj) | tathāuparipi pariññā (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.60:0.3"
msgid "60. Sabbupādānapariññāsutta"
msgstr "60. The Complete Understanding of All Grasping"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.33"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.60:1.1"
msgid "“Sabbupādānapariññāya vo, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ desessāmi."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, I will teach you the principle for the complete understanding "
"of all grasping."

msgctxt "sn35.60:1.2"
msgid "Taṃ suṇātha."
msgstr "Listen …"

#. VAR: sabbupādānapariññāya → sabbūpādānapariññāya (bj)
msgctxt "sn35.60:1.3"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sabbupādānapariññāya dhammo?"
msgstr ""
"And what is the principle for the complete understanding of all grasping?"

msgctxt "sn35.60:1.4"
msgid ""
"Cakkhuñca paṭicca rūpe ca uppajjati cakkhuviññāṇaṃ. Tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso."
msgstr ""
"Eye consciousness arises dependent on the eye and sights. The meeting of the "
"three is contact."

msgctxt "sn35.60:1.5"
msgid "Phassapaccayā vedanā."
msgstr "Contact is a condition for feeling."

msgctxt "sn35.60:1.6"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ passaṃ, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako cakkhusmimpi nibbindati, rūpesupi "
"nibbindati, cakkhuviññāṇepi nibbindati, cakkhusamphassepi nibbindati, "
"vedanāyapi nibbindati."
msgstr ""
"Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with the eye, "
"sights, eye consciousness, eye contact, and feeling."

#. VAR: vimokkhā → vimokkha (s1-3, km) | vimokkhaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "sn35.60:1.7"
msgid ""
"Nibbindaṃ virajjati; virāgā vimuccati; vimokkhā ‘pariññātaṃ me upādānan’ti "
"pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re "
"freed. When they are released, they understand: ‘I have completely "
"understood grasping.’"

msgctxt "sn35.60:1.8"
msgid "Sotañca paṭicca sadde ca uppajjati …"
msgstr "Ear consciousness arises dependent on the ear and sounds. …"

msgctxt "sn35.60:1.9"
msgid "ghānañca paṭicca gandhe ca …"
msgstr "Nose consciousness arises dependent on the nose and smells. …"

msgctxt "sn35.60:1.10"
msgid "jivhañca paṭicca rase ca …"
msgstr "Tongue consciousness arises dependent on the tongue and tastes. …"

msgctxt "sn35.60:1.11"
msgid "kāyañca paṭicca phoṭṭhabbe ca …"
msgstr "Body consciousness arises dependent on the body and touches. …"

msgctxt "sn35.60:1.12"
msgid ""
"manañca paṭicca dhamme ca uppajjati manoviññāṇaṃ. Tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso."
msgstr ""
"Mind consciousness arises dependent on the mind and thoughts. The meeting of "
"the three is contact."

msgctxt "sn35.60:1.13"
msgid "Phassapaccayā vedanā."
msgstr "Contact is a condition for feeling."

msgctxt "sn35.60:1.14"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ passaṃ, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako manasmimpi nibbindati, dhammesupi "
"nibbindati, manoviññāṇepi nibbindati, manosamphassepi nibbindati, vedanāyapi "
"nibbindati."
msgstr ""
"Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with the mind, "
"thoughts, mind consciousness, mind contact, and feeling."

msgctxt "sn35.60:1.15"
msgid ""
"Nibbindaṃ virajjati; virāgā vimuccati; vimokkhā ‘pariññātaṃ me upādānan’ti "
"pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re "
"freed. When they are released, they understand: ‘I have completely "
"understood grasping.’"

msgctxt "sn35.60:1.16"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhave, sabbupādānapariññāya dhammo”ti."
msgstr "This is the principle for the complete understanding of all grasping.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.60:1.17"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
